		raw-html:<p>Unit 6 completes students' preparation for the AP exam with topics about the software and hardware that make a computer work. As usual, the organizing principle is abstraction both in the structure of a computer system (Lab 1) and in the representation of data (Lab 2).
	raw-html: <p><strong>Social Implication Focus:</strong> Global Impact of Computing Review</p>
		raw-html: Unit 6 also reviews the global impact of computing, adding new elements needed for the AP and putting some familiar ones in a new perspective.</p>
		
h3: Big Ideas
